MOST IMM
No.1/34/1/2012-Cab.
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 22nd September, 2012
The undersigned is directed to say that with effect from the 22nd
September, 2012:
(i)
Shri Mukul Roy relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Railways;
Shri C.P. Joshi assumed the additional charge of the office of the Minister of Railways.
(ii)
He will continue to hold the charge of the office of the Minister of Road Transport and
Highways;
(iii) Shri Saugata Ray relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Urban Development;
(iv) Shri Sisir Adhikari relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Rural Development;
(v)
Shri Sultan Ahmed relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Tourism;
(vi) Shri Choudhury Mohan Jatua relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of
State in the Ministry of information and Broadcasting; and
(vii) Shri Sudip Bandyopadhyay relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State
in the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare.
(K.L. SKarma)
for Cabinet Secretary
Tele : 2301 5802
To
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
Copy forwarded for information to the Deputy Chairman and Members of the Planning
Commission.
(K.L. Sharma)
